cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

The paper focuses on a computer vision task of human-object interaction detection, which falls under the category of visual relationship detection. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed approach leverages context information to improve the performance, which involves learning contextually-aware features and using an attention module. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed approach involves object localization, which is a common task in robotics, suggesting that the paper may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the experiments are performed on three benchmarks, which suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
